{% extends 'layouts/default' %}
{% block csshead %}
<style>
  .page-subhead {
    text-transform: uppercase
  }

  .main-box {
    padding-top: 40px;
  }

  .donate {
    /*padding: 50px */
    background-color: #fff;
    width: 500px;
    color: #000;
  }

  .donate p {
    line-height: 24px;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .donate h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 300;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }

  .denomination {
    float: left;
    width: 33%;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 13px 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    background-color: #fff;
    margin: 0 1px 1px 0;
  }

  .denomination label {
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .denomination input {
    left: -10001px;
    position: absolute;
  }

  .denomination-other {
    width: 99.8%;
  }

  .denomination-other input {
    color: #000;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    width: inherit;
    text-align: center;
    background-color: #C51162;
    border: none;
    padding: 13px 0;
  }

  .denomination-other input:hover {
    background-color: #D81B60;
  }

  .donate-amount .selected, .donate-amount .denomination:hover {
    background-color: #D81B60;
    border: 0;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .donate-black h2 {
    color: #000;
    font-size: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }

  .donate-black h2 span {
    display: block;
    float: left;
    font-size: 16px;
    padding-top: 7px;
    margin-right: 20px;
    text-align: center;
    width: 30px;
    height: 25px;
    background-color: #D81B60;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .donate-type label,
  .donate-payment label {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 300;
    margin-right: 30px;
  }

  .donate-blue {
    background-color: #FF80AB;
    padding: 25px;
  }

  .donate-black {
    padding: 25px;
  }

  .donate-submit button {
    width: 100%;
    background-color: #D81B60;
    border: none;
    color: #FFF;
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 20px;
    padding: 14px 0;
    margin: 30px 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .donate-submit small {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  ::-webkit-input-placeholder {
    color: #FFF;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  :-moz-placeholder {
    color: #FFF;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  ::-moz-placeholder {
    color: #FFF;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  :-ms-input-placeholder {
    font-weight: 300;
    color: #FFF;
  }

  *:focus {
    outline: none;
  }

  /* --- DONATION MODAL STYLING --- */


</style>
{% endblock %}
{% block jshead %}{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<div class="box-component">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row py-3">
      <div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
        <h3 class="page-subhead mb-0"> When you give, you always get!</h3>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="box-component main-box">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-12">
        <p>This holds absolutely true when you talk about donations. While you give away with a golden heart, you also save
          goodness to your account. And while you will be paying off a part of your money, you will be happy to know that
          not only its going to give you satisfaction, but let you out a sigh of relief because Hey! You might get tax exemption!</p>

        <p>You heard it absolutely right! To encourage more donations for the social causes and ensuring that taxes dont turn
          the smile on your face while you do it, upside down, the government of India under the Section 80G, Chapter 6A
          of the Income Tax Act gives tax exemption on donations in certain certified NGOs.</p>

        <p>
          <h4>Not every NGO</h4>
        </p>

        <p>Donation in just any NGO will not provide you the benefit of the exemption. NGOs and institutions you donate in should
          be registered with the Income-tax department through 12A, with tax exemption status under section 80G, 80 GGA,
          35 ac (i & ii), (i & iii) of the Income Tax Act of 1961.</p>

        <p>
          <h4>Who Can Donate?</h4>
        </p>

        <p>The person donating to an Indian NGO and claiming for the exemption on tax has to be a resident of India or a Non-Resident
          Indian holding an Indian Passport with a taxable income in India.</p>

        <p>
          <h5>DEDUCTION RATES AND HOW YOU QUALIFY</h5>
        </p>

        <p>While you donate with the registered NGOs, a certain amount is qualified for the tax deduction under Section 80G.
          The donation will qualify for deduction only up to the limit of 10% of the Gross Total Income – GTI. Within which
          again there are limits that some donations qualify for the deduction at the rate of 100% and some qualify at the
          rate of 50%.</p>

        <p>As per the amendments to the Finance Act 2017, cash donations exceeding Rs 2000, unless by means other than cash,
          will not be eligible for the tax benefit. While donations for rural development are concerned, cash donations beyond
          Rs 10,000 will not be eligible under section 80CGA.</p>

        <p>
          <h5>PROOF OF PAYMENTS AND DEDUCTION</h5>
        </p>

        <p>While after the donation, proof of payment must be submitted to claim the deduction. Were pushing towards a cash-free
          economy; it is advisable to make donations by a cheque or demand draft than by cash. Do note, that current budget
          has restricted the tax benefit on cash donations to the limit of Rs 10,000 only.</p>

        <p>Also, it is advisable to take note of the PAN card number of the institution youre donating it. It will be needed
          while filing the tax returns and will also go for the record purposes.</p>

        <p>
          <b>Now that you know that making a donation wont rip your pocket away with taxes, its time to do some good.</b>
        </p>

        <div class="col-sm-12 text-center pt-4">
          <div class="col-sm-12">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-custom-designed" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#donateModal">Donate</button>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="donateModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="exampleModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog" role="document" style="margin-top: 6em;">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="donate">
        <div class="donate-black">
          <h2>
            Donate
          </h2>
          <p>Your contribution is vital to the success of our initiative.</p>
          <p>Choose the amount you wish to donate with paypal, as one-time or monthly payment.</p>
        </div>
        <form action="{{ url('/') }}postVolunteer" method="POST">
          <input type="hidden" value="{{ user.id }}" name="user_id"/>
          <input type="hidden" value="{{ project_id }}" name="project_id"/>
          <div class="donate-blue">
            <h3>Donation amount*</h3>
              <div class="donate-amount-box">
                <div class="donate-amount">
                  <div class="denomination selected">
                    <input autocomplete="off" type="radio" name="amount" id="amount5000" value="5000" data-value="5,000" checked="">
                    <label for="amount5000">₹5,000</label>
                  </div>
                  <div class="denomination">
                    <input autocomplete="off" type="radio" id="amount10000" value="10000" data-value="10,000" checked="">
                    <label for="amount10000">₹10,000</label>
                  </div>
                  <div class="denomination">
                    <input autocomplete="off" type="radio" id="amount15000" value="15000" data-value="15,000">
                    <label for="amount15000">₹15,000</label>
                  </div>
                  <div class="denomination">
                    <input autocomplete="off" type="radio" id="amount25000" value="25000" data-value="25,000">
                    <label for="amount25000">₹25,000</label>
                  </div>
                  <div class="denomination">
                    <input autocomplete="off" type="radio" id="amount50000" value="50000" data-value="50,000">
                    <label for="amount50000">₹50,000</label>
                  </div>
                  <div class="denomination">
                    <input autocomplete="off" type="radio" id="amount100000" value="100000" data-value="1,00,000">
                    <label for="amount100">₹1,00,000</label>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="denomination-other">
                  <input autocomplete="off" type="text" value="" placeholder="Enter Other Amount">
                </div>
              </div>
          </div>
          <div class="donate-black donate-type">
            <h3>Donation type*</h3>
            <label>
              <input type="radio" name="donation_type" value="single" checked="checked" autocomplete="off" class="required"> One-Time
            </label>
          </div>
          <div class="donate-blue donate-payment">
            <h3>Payment Method</h3>
            <div>
              <label>
                <input type="radio" name="paytm" value="1" checked="checked" autocomplete="off">PayTM
              </label>
            </div>
            <div class="donate-submit">
              <button type="submit" autocomplete="off">Donate ₹5,000</button>
              <p>
                <small>Most contributions earn you tax benefits</small>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>


    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{% endblock %}
{% block jsfooter %}
<script>
  $(function () {

    $('.denomination').on('click', function(e) {
      let amount = $(this).find('input').attr('data-value')

      $('.denomination').removeClass('selected')
      $('.denomination').find('input').removeAttr('name')
      console.log($('.denomination').find('input'))
      $(this).addClass('selected')

      $(this).find('input').attr('name', 'amount')
      $('.donate-submit').find('button').html(`Donate &#8377; ${amount}`)
    })

    $('.denomination-other').find('input').on('focus', function(e) {
      $('.donate-submit').find('button').html(`Donate`)
      $('.denomination').find('input').removeAttr('name')

      $(this).attr('name', 'amount')
    })

  });
</script>
{% endblock %}